The Nifty50 index managed to hold its crucial 9,150-mark last week and settled 24.55 points, or 0.27 per cent higher at 9,198.30 on April 7 against 9,173.75 on March 31, 2017. Overall, the index commenced the truncated week on a gap up note. However, after marking all-time high of 9,274 during the week, markets witnessed some correction in the last two days due to some profit and weak global cues.

